Given a list of integers, write a C++ program to find the sum of all the even numbers in the list. 
Please provide your implementation and explanation for how you arrived at that answer. 
Input data: 
int numList[] = {4, 7, 2, 1, 9, 8, 3};
Input code: 
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
  int numList[] = {4, 7, 2, 1, 9, 8, 3};
  int sum = 0;
  for(int i=0; i<sizeof(numList)/sizeof(numList[0]); i++){
    if(numList[i]%2==0){
      sum += numList[i];
    }
  }
  cout<<"The sum of all even numbers in the list is: "<<sum<<endl;
  return 0;
}
Note: Please provide your implementation and explanation using only text, and refrain from using any programming language-specific syntax.
